== Potatoes ==

Boil a full #kettle{} of water.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

Pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Add the potatoes to the pan and cook until you can easily slip a knife through,
~{15-18%minutes}.

== Chicken and Mushrooms ==

While the potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{}
on high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and
@sliced mushrooms{180%g} to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until the chicken is golden brown on the outside and cooked through,
~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Garlic Creamy Sauce ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Once the chicken and mushrooms are cooked through, add the garlic to the pan.
Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water{100%ml} to the pan, then bring to
the boil and reduce by half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir through the @creme fraiche{75%g} and @wholegrain mustard{17%g} until
everything's piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Mash ==

Meanwhile, once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to
the pan, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @milk{splash} (if you have any).
Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth.

Season with salt and pepper. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, spoon the mash into your #bowls{}.

Share out the creamy mustard chicken alongside. Enjoy!